    <h6></h6>
    <div style="max-width:75ch">
      <p>Welcome to my home page!</p>

      <p>
I develop computational frameworks to study complex systems that emerge from
large-scale interactions across diverse domains, including infectious disease
dynamics, socio-environmental resilience, agriculture, and other socio-technical systems.
Central to my research are the
development of realistic synthetic datasets (like digital twins) and
data-driven simulation models, the design of domain-informed algorithms,
and the advancement of theoretical foundations underlying these complex
systems.
This research draws on and contributes to network science, simulation modeling,
algorithm design, and machine learning.       </p>
      <p>
        My work takes place in interdisciplinary team environments and has been supported by multiple funding agencies. I have led USDA- and USAID-funded projects that address real-world socio-technical challenges.
      </p>

